I would suggest you use completion instead of DispatchGroup. You will use it way more in the future, so you better master it:

P.S: Name your functions names and variables names in a camel case way. It is the norm in Swift language.

```
func readMyData(completion: () -&gt; ()) {
        
    let data = Firestore.firestore().collection(&quot;users&quot;).document(&quot;LdGcPDsSVEtYyrGIHR1D&quot;)
        
    data.getDocument { (document, error) in
            
        for item in (document?.data())! {
            self.myArray.append(item.key) //using Array as the name of an array is bad practice.
        }
        print(myArray)
        completion()
    }
}
```
When you will call this function, you will be able to do your next action when the completion is called, thus ensuring that all your data manipulations, in this case, appending to your array, is completed before doing the next actions.

